results.name: Decimal expansion of product_{n>=2} (1-n^(-5)).
formula: Equals product_{t=1..4} 1/Gamma(2-exp(2*Pi*i*t/5)), where i is the imaginary unit.

Equals 1/(Gamma(2 + phi/2 - i*(5^(1/4) / (2*sqrt(phi)))) * Gamma(2 + phi/2 + i*(5^(1/4) / (2*sqrt(phi)))) * Gamma(2 - 1/(2*phi) - i*5^(1/4)*(sqrt(phi)/2)) * Gamma(2 - 1/(2*phi) + i*5^(1/4)*(sqrt(phi)/2))), where phi = A001622 = (1+sqrt(5))/2 is the golden ratio and i is the imaginary unit. - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Dec 15 2020
mathematica: g[k_] := Gamma[Root[1 - # + #^2 - #^3 + #^4 & , k]]; RealDigits[ 1/(5*g[1]*g[2]*g[3]*g[4]) // Re, 10, 105] // First (* _Jean-François Alcover_, Feb 12 2013 *)
